```
2. compile and run the extension, then restart/shutdown pc, and check if the file file_deactivate_something was created

The implementation does not handle `null | undefined` and imho should also not handle it actually.

Somewhat depends on https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/70491

//cc @mjbvz @isidorn

```ts
enum WaitOnExitType {
    Never = 0,
    NonZeroExitCode = 1,
    Always = 2
}

export interface TerminalOptions {
    /**
     * Whether the terminal panel should wait before closing when a terminal's process exits.
     */
    waitOnExit?: WaitOnExitType;
}
```

waitOnExit was originally proposed as a boolean in https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/15583
